results.name: a(n) is the number of partitions of n into 2 distinct positive cubes.
comment: In other words, number of solutions to the equation n = x^3 + y^3 with x > y > 0. The first value > 1 is a(1729) = 2. - _Antti Karttunen_, Aug 29 2017
